-41, \"text\": \"Omnium\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Omnium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Omnium\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The session kicks off with the first event in the women's Omnium, the scratch race, at 11:00 local time (CET), with the tempo race at 11:57, the elimination race at 12:53, and finally the points race at 13:56.\", \"from\": 2231, \"to\": 2440, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2289, \"end\": 2295, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Omnium\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.178593999982922e-41, \"text\": \"Omnium\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Omnium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Omnium\"}, {\"begin\": 2336, \"end\": 2339, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Central_European_Time\", \"score\": 0.9999999800347725, \"rank\": 1.9964796095212e-08, \"text\": \"CET\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Central_European_Time\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Central_European_Time\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The women's Sprint semifinals start at 11:22, with the finals starting at 12:45 for the first heats and the second heats coming at 13:15.\", \"from\": 2442, \"to\": 2579, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2454, \"end\": 2460, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sprint_Corporation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.243755528253281e-21, \"text\": \"Sprint\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sprint_Corporation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sprint_Corporation\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If deciders are needed, they will be at 13:44.\", \"from\": 2580, \"to\": 2626, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The men's Keirin sees the quarterfinal at 11:29, the semifinals at 12:29, and the finals at 13:23.\", \"from\": 2627, \"to\": 2725, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2637, \"end\": 2643, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keirin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.717934022883868e-62, \"text\": \"Keirin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keirin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keirin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This guide explains how to watch Olympics Track Cycling 2024 wherever you are in the world, including details ofhow to use a VPNif you are away from home.\", \"from\": 2727, \"to\": 2881, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For more from the other disciplines, find outhow to watch cycling at the Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 2882, \"to\": 2970, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The latest race content, interviews, features, reviews and expert buying guides, direct to your inbox!\", \"from\": 2972, \"to\": 3074, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"NBC holds the broadcasting rights for the Olympic Games in the USA.\", \"from\": 3076, \"to\": 3143, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3076, \"end\": 3079, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.9980986119764478, \"rank\": 0.0019050049602937224, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 3139, \"end\": 3142, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Network\", \"score\": 0.999935143556804, \"rank\": 6.486065008232297e-05, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Network\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Network\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympics will be shown across several of the the broadcaster's television channels, and also on the network's streaming service,Peacock.\", \"from\": 3144, \"to\": 3284, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3276, \"end\": 3283, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"score\": 0.9999999852561815, \"rank\": 1.474315828860608e-08, \"text\": \"Peacock\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All the track cycling, from the preliminary rounds to the finals, is available on Peacock, which offers a seven-day free trial for those who want to try before they buy.\", \"from\": 3286, \"to\": 3455, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3368, \"end\": 3375, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"score\": 0.9999999852561815, \"rank\": 1.474315828860608e-08, \"text\": \"Peacock\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A full subscription to the service via Peacock Premium starts from $7.99 per month.\", \"from\": 3456, \"to\": 3539, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3495, \"end\": 3510, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peacock_(streaming_service)\", \"score\": 0.9999999936162567, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Peacock Premium\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peacock_(streaming_service)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peacock_(streaming_service)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The ad-free Peacock Premium Plus costs $13.99 per month.\", \"from\": 3540, \"to\": 3596, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The finals for each event will also be shown live on television across four channels: USA Network, E!, CNBC, and NBC 4 New York.\", \"from\": 3598, \"to\": 3726, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3684, \"end\": 3695, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCSN\", \"score\": 0.9999933579622425, \"rank\": 6.642081997322504e-06, \"text\": \"USA Network\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCSN\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCSN\"}, {\"begin\": 3701, \"end\": 3705, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNBC\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.987346650719555e-20, \"text\": \"CNBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNBC\"}, {\"begin\": 3711, \"end\": 3714, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.9980986119764478, \"rank\": 0.0019050049602937224, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 3711, \"end\": 3725, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WNBC\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NBC 4 New York\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WNBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WNBC\"}, {\"begin\": 3711, \"end\": 3725, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WNBC\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NBC 4 New York\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WNBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WNBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These channels are available via cable plans, but there is no need to worry if you do not have cable.Slingis a smart TV service that allows people in the US to watch cable channels on their TV, laptop or tablet without actually having to subscribe to an annual cable TV package.\", \"from\": 3728, \"to\": 4006, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3882, \"end\": 3884, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_dollar\", \"score\": 0.9999979736560429, \"rank\": 2.026348269856784e-06, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_dollar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_dollar\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"USA Network and E!\", \"from\": 4007, \"to\": 4025, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4007, \"end\": 4018, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCSN\", \"score\": 0.9999933579622425, \"rank\": 6.642081997322504e-06, \"text\": \"USA Network\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCSN\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCSN\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"are available on Sling with the Sling Blue package, which costs $40 per month ($20 for the first month).\", \"from\": 4026, \"to\": 4130, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"CNBC is available with the News Extra add-on to Sling Blue, costing $6 per month.\", \"from\": 4131, \"to\": 4212, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4131, \"end\": 4135, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNBC\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.987346650719555e-20, \"text\": \"CNBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNBC\"}, {\"begin\": 4179, \"end\": 4184, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sling_TV\", \"score\": 0.9997032615379977, \"rank\": 0.00029682654216406373, \"text\": \"Sling\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sling_TV\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sling_TV\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If you live in Canada, you can catch the Olympics across several broadcasters, including the free-to-air CBC, and subscription services TSN and Sportsnet.\", \"from\": 4214, \"to\": 4368, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4229, \"end\": 4235, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.999999999996362, \"rank\": 3.3659785505282846e-12, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}, {\"begin\": 4350, \"end\": 4353, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Sports_Network\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.491578538684652e-16, \"text\": \"TSN\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Sports_Network\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Sports_Network\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's not yet clear which exact Track Cycling events will be included as part ofCBC's live television coverage but, as in the USA, finals are likely to be shown.\", \"from\": 4370, \"to\": 4530, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4495, \"end\": 4498, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Network\", \"score\": 0.999935143556804, \"rank\": 6.486065008232297e-05, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Network\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Network\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There will be extensive coverage of all the action online onCBC Gem.\", \"from\": 4531, \"to\": 4599, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Access to the broadcaster's ad-free premium service costs $5.99 per month, though the ad-supported version is free of charge.\", \"from\": 4600, \"to\": 4725, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"TSN and Sportsnet do not have dedicated streams for each sport, so it's not certain how much track cycling will be shown on their daily coverage, although finals and races with a Canadian interest are likely to make the cut.\", \"from\": 4727, \"to\": 4951, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4727, \"end\": 4730, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Sports_Network\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.491578538684652e-16, \"text\": \"TSN\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Sports_Network\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Sports_Network\"}, {\"begin\": 4906, \"end\": 4914, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Television_in_Canada\", \"score\": 0.9979522051028852, \"rank\": 0.0020519968467103407, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Television_in_Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Television_in_Canada\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"TheTSNsubscription service will set you back $19.99 per month or $199.90 per year.\", \"from\": 4953, \"to\": 5035, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, aSportsnet SN Nowsubscription costs $14.99 per month or $179.99 per year.\", \"from\": 5036, \"to\": 5120, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5058, \"end\": 5060, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sportsnet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.41528651918893e-21, \"text\": \"SN\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sportsnet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sportsnet\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the UK, cycling fans will be able to watch the Olympics on the BBC for free, via BBC One, BBC Two andBBC iPlayer.\", \"from\": 5122, \"to\": 5238, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5129, \"end\": 5131, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999999999899956, \"rank\": 5.1191681235742415e-12, \"text\": \"UK\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 5188, \"end\": 5191, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_Sport\", \"score\": 0.9999966873447491, \"rank\": 3.3101356832048463e-06, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_Sport\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The BBC only has rights to broadcast two streams at any one time, however, so while the track cycling will be heavily favoured by the national broadcaster, given the number of Brits involved and medals at stake, it's not guaranteed that every round of every event will be shown.\", \"from\": 5240, \"to\": 5518, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5244, \"end\": 5247, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_Sport\", \"score\": 0.9999966873447491, \"rank\": 3.3101356832048463e-06, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_Sport\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For that, you will have to watch onDiscovery+, home to the most comprehensive coverage in the UK - 3,800 hours of live action across 55 channels.\", \"from\": 5520, \"to\": 5665, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5614, \"end\": 5616, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999999999899956, \"rank\": 5.1191681235742415e-12, \"text\": \"UK\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thanks to aspecial Olympics dealyou can subscribe to the \\\"standard\\\" Discovery+ package for a cut-price \\u00a33.99 per month - sign up before August 11 and you can take advantage of the lower price until the end of the year.\", \"from\": 5667, \"to\": 5885, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The package includes year-round cycling streams as well as other live sports, including snooker, tennis, motorsports, and more.\", \"from\": 5886, \"to\": 6013, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In Australia, cycling fans can watch the Olympics for free onChannel 9and its9Now streaming service- arguably the most comprehensive free Olympics coverage in the world.\", \"from\": 6015, \"to\": 6184, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6018, \"end\": 6027, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9999999980627763, \"rank\": 1.8343892391272771e-09, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As is the case in other territories, a good chunk of the action is expected to be included in live television broadcast, but for guaranteed coverage of all the track cycling, fans can head to 9Now on the smart device of their choosing.\", \"from\": 6186, \"to\": 6421, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If you are travelling abroad and try to access your usual live streaming services to watch the action, you may find your access to be geo-restricted.\", \"from\": 6423, \"to\": 6572, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In this case, a VPN service will come in handy, allowing your computer to pretend it's home and let you log into your streaming accounts to catch all of the racing action.\", \"from\": 6574, \"to\": 6745, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Our colleagues atTechRadarthoroughly tested several VPNservices and NordVPN won the gold medal:  NordVPN - get the world's favorite VPNWe've put all the major VPNs through their paces and we rate NordVPN as the best for streaming Netflix as our top pick, thanks to its speed, ease of use and strong security features.\", \"from\": 6747, \"to\": 7064, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6977, \"end\": 6984, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netflix\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3085364933302693e-36, \"text\": \"Netflix\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netflix\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netflix\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's also compatible with just about any streaming device out there, including Amazon Fire TV Stick, Apple TV, Xbox and PlayStation, as well as Android and Apple mobiles.\", \"from\": 7065, \"to\": 7235, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7144, \"end\": 7164, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amazon_Fire_TV\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Amazon Fire TV Stick\", \"types\": [\"Q1067263\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amazon_Fire_TV\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amazon_Fire_TV\"}, {\"begin\": 7166, \"end\": 7174, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_TV\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.291694341503872e-14, \"text\": \"Apple TV\", \"types\": [\"Q1067263\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_TV\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_TV\"}, {\"begin\": 7176, \"end\": 7180, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xbox_360\", \"score\": 0.8585221695273111, \"rank\": 0.16058167747386562, \"text\": \"Xbox\", \"types\": [\"Q1067263\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xbox_360\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xbox_360\"}, {\"begin\": 7209, \"end\": 7216, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Play\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1703123611589754e-33, \"text\": \"Android\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Play\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Play\"}, {\"begin\": 7221, \"end\": 7226, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.369294302974267e-39, \"text\": \"Apple\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We test and review VPN services in the context of legal recreational uses.\", \"from\": 7237, \"to\": 7311, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For example: 1.\", \"from\": 7312, \"to\": 7327, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Accessing a service from another country (subject to the terms and conditions of that service).\", \"from\": 7328, \"to\": 7423, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"2.\", \"from\": 7424, \"to\": 7426, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Protecting your online security and strengthening your online privacy when abroad.\", \"from\": 7427, \"to\": 7509, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We do not support or condone the illegal or malicious use of VPN services.\", \"from\": 7510, \"to\": 7584, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Consuming pirated content that is paid-for is neither endorsed nor approved by Future Publishing.\", \"from\": 7585, \"to\": 7682, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7664, \"end\": 7681, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Future_plc\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.887914681964639e-19, \"text\": \"Future Publishing\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Future_plc\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Future_plc\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Patrick is an NCTJ-accredited journalist with a bachelor's degree in modern languages (French and Spanish) and a decade's experience in digital sports media, largely within the world of cycling.\", \"from\": 7684, \"to\": 7878, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7684, \"end\": 7691, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Danica_Patrick\", \"score\": 0.9930289252289454, \"rank\": 0.00701879766214776, \"text\": \"Patrick\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q378622\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Danica_Patrick\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Danica_Patrick\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He re-joined Cyclingnews as Deputy Editor in February 2026, having previously spent eight years on staff between 2015 and 2023.\", \"from\": 7879, \"to\": 8006, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7892, \"end\": 7903, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cyclingnews.com\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Cyclingnews\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cyclingnews.com\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cyclingnews.com\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In between, he was Deputy Editor at GCN and spent 18 months working across the sports portfolio at Future before returning to the cycling press pack.\", \"from\": 8007, \"to\": 8156, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8043, \"end\": 8046, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/GameCube\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.09728243084128e-17, \"text\": \"GCN\", \"types\": [\"Q1067263\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/GameCube\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/GameCube\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Patrick works across Cyclingnews' wide-ranging output, assisting the Editor in global content strategy, with a particular focus on shaping CN's news operation.\", \"from\": 8157, \"to\": 8316, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8157, \"end\": 8164, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Danica_Patrick\", \"score\": 0.9930289252289454, \"rank\": 0.00701879766214776, \"text\": \"Patrick\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q378622\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Danica_Patrick\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Danica_Patrick\"}, {\"begin\": 8178, \"end\": 8189, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cyclingnews.com\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\